{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":14553,"record_hash":"sha256:81c93ddc7127ae21c6947c9d664724963f245d3ee14c3f289a02a4cfa0122d49","timestamp":"2026-05-09T17:57:01.423Z","kind":"tool_call","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:custom_tool_call","role":null,"text":null,"tool_name":"apply_patch","tool_input":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Delete File: /Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/agent-session-capture/architecture.md\n*** Add File: /Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/agent-session-capture/architecture.md\n+# Architecture\n+\n+## Crate Boundary\n+\n+`crates/but-agentlog` owns agent log capture and GitMeta writes.\n+\n+It should not depend on `but-api`, `but-db`, `but-ctx`, `but-claude`,\n+`but-cursor`, workspace rules, or legacy virtual-branch APIs. The POC should use\n+a closed `Agent` enum and explicit Codex/Claude parser branches, not a plugin\n+framework.\n+\n+## POC Boundary\n+\n+For the first implementation:\n+\n+- support Codex and Claude only\n+- require explicit `--transcript-path`\n+- default to the `project` GitMeta target\n+- write redacted, shareable-ready `gitbutler:*` keys\n+- do not discover sessions\n+- do not infer branch, change, commit, or pull request ownership\n+- do not serialize, push, fetch, or sync GitMeta\n+\n+If this file conflicts with [First POC Implementation Contract](first-poc-implementation.md),\n+the implementation contract wins.\n+\n+## CLI Integration\n+\n+The `but` crate should expose only the hidden top-level hook:\n+\n+```text\n+but agentlog capture ...\n+```\n+\n+The command shape and argument mapping live in `but-agentlog`. The `but` crate\n+should remain limited to feature-gating, output mode selection, and delegation.\n+\n+Without the `agentlog` feature, the command is not compiled or recognized. With\n+the feature enabled, it is callable but hidden from help.\n+\n+## Module Ownership\n+\n+Keep ownership narrow:\n+\n+- `cli.rs`: hidden command type and CLI-to-capture mapping\n+- `capture.rs`: orchestration, repository-safe source identity, cwd validation\n+- `transcript.rs`: Codex/Claude JSONL parsing and normalized record extraction\n+- `gitmeta.rs`: GitMeta target/key/value writes and transcript envelope storage\n+- `redaction.rs`: string/value redaction only\n+\n+Avoid adding abstractions unless a second concrete use in the POC needs them.\n+\n+## Capture Pipeline\n+\n+```text\n+CLI command\n+  -> resolve repository and explicit transcript path\n+  -> parse transcript snapshot\n+  -> validate transcript cwd values\n+  -> derive durable session/source keys\n+  -> write GitMeta session metadata, record hashes, and transcript envelopes\n+  -> return terse output\n+```\n+\n+The transcript parser should not write GitMeta. The GitMeta writer should not\n+know provider-specific transcript shapes beyond the normalized record it\n+receives.\n+\n+## Target And Associations\n+\n+The durable session object should stay on the `project` target by default. Even\n+when future code can identify a branch, change, commit, or pull request, those\n+objects should reference project session keys rather than own transcript data.\n+\n+That keeps session handoff possible before code exists and avoids bad ownership\n+guesses when one agent session contributes to multiple GitButler branches.\n+\n+Future relationship keys can look like:\n+\n+```text\n+<branch/change/commit target>\n+  gitbutler:agent-sessions = set<session-key>\n+```\n+\n+## GitMeta Writer\n+\n+The writer is the only code that should depend directly on `git-meta-lib`.\n+\n+Responsibilities:\n+\n+- open `git_meta_lib::Session`\n+- resolve a `git_meta_lib::Target`\n+- maintain `gitbutler:agent-sessions = set<session-key>`\n+- write session keys under `gitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:*`\n+- append redacted transcript envelopes\n+- keep metadata hashes and transcript envelope hashes separate enough for\n+  idempotent repeated capture and transcript backfill\n+\n+The writer should return a report and never print.\n+\n+## Privacy Boundary\n+\n+Capture writes shareable-ready keys but does not publish them. Serialization,\n+push, fetch, and sync require a later privacy/product decision.\n+\n+Even before publishing, transcripts are sensitive. The POC should redact copied\n+strings before storage and should not store full transcript paths, cwd values,\n+branch names, or raw provider session ids.\n+\n*** End Patch\n","source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-09T17:57:01.423Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","status":"completed","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]","name":"apply_patch"}}}